		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=314343"><span id=>MariuzDevereux</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br />2 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=MariuzDevereux&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>I am in the same boat as you.&nbsp;&nbsp;I just recently got a bard to 20's.  I started playing a bard, but then gave him up for a druid.  Now with /melody i don't have to kill my wrists (even though i've seen melody is only useful sometimes).  <br><br>Anyways, Your plan for where to level was roughly the same as what i planned to do... i'll throw in some places that might help bridge the gaps.<br><br>1-20: PC (Start @ the back entrance through Shadeweavers Thicket)<br>21-30: High Hold Keep <br>25-35: Dawn Shroud Peek<br>30-40: Marus Seru (i think this might be lower level actually)<br>25-35: OT<br>30-40: Eastern Wastes (Ulthorks are great exp + 4 tusks = blue diamond)<br>35-46: DL, gunthak, dulak<br>46-50: PoJustice<br>51-54: PoInnovation<br>55-61: PoValor<br><br>Of course i've found the best and fastest way to level was doing Hard LDoN's.  At lower level's they are relatively easy.  Lowbies normally have much better equipment than what they *should* have if they were that level, so i remember being able to tank a hard LDoN with my ranger til about lev 45-50, so any group should really be able.  Points, aug upgrade, possible drops, cash, tradeskill items... and fast exp.  Mind you i don't know much about OOW zones at lower levels.<br><br></p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />[70 Natureguard] -Prophet Mariuz Devereux &lt;Moonlight Crusaders&gt;<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=817183" target="akztarg">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=817183</a><br></td></td></tr><tr><td